verses.text: Now Joshua was old \add and\add* stricken in years ; and the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto him, Thou art old \add and\add* stricken in years , and there remaineth yet very much land to be possessed.\f + \fr 13.1 \ft to…: Heb. to possess it\f*
This \add is\add* the land that yet remaineth : all the borders of the Philistines , and all Geshuri ,

From Sihor , which \add is\add* before Egypt , even unto the borders of Ekron northward , \add which\add* is counted to the Canaanite : five lords of the Philistines ; the Gazathites , and the Ashdothites , the Eshkalonites , the Gittites , and the Ekronites ; also the Avites :
From the south , all the land of the Canaanites , and Mearah that \add is\add* beside the Sidonians , unto Aphek , to the borders of the Amorites :\f + \fr 13.4 \ft Mearah: or, the cave\f*
And the land of the Giblites , and all Lebanon , toward the sunrising , from Baal-gad under mount Hermon unto the entering into Hamath.

All the inhabitants of the hill country from Lebanon unto Misrephoth-maim , \add and\add* all the Sidonians , them will I drive out from before the children of Israel : only divide thou it by lot unto the Israelites for an inheritance , as I have commanded thee. \p
Now therefore divide this land for an inheritance unto the nine tribes , and the half tribe of Manasseh ,

With whom the Reubenites and the Gadites have received their inheritance , which Moses gave them, beyond Jordan eastward , \add even\add* as Moses the servant of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* gave them;
From Aroer , that \add is\add* upon the bank of the river Arnon , and the city that \add is\add* in the midst of the river , and all the plain of Medeba unto Dibon ;
And all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites , which reigned in Heshbon , unto the border of the children of Ammon ;
And Gilead , and the border of the Geshurites and Maachathites , and all mount Hermon , and all Bashan unto Salcah ;
All the kingdom of Og in Bashan , which reigned in Ashtaroth and in Edrei , who remained of the remnant of the giants : for these did Moses smite , and cast them out.
Nevertheless the children of Israel expelled not the Geshurites , nor the Maachathites : but the Geshurites and the Maachathites dwell among the Israelites until this day.
Only unto the tribe of Levi he gave none inheritance ; the sacrifices of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of Israel made by fire \add are\add* their inheritance , as he said unto them. \p
¶ And Moses gave unto the tribe of the children of Reuben \add inheritance\add* according to their families.
And their coast was from Aroer , that \add is\add* on the bank of the river Arnon , and the city that \add is\add* in the midst of the river , and all the plain by Medeba ;
Heshbon , and all her cities that \add are\add* in the plain ; Dibon , and Bamoth-baal , and Beth-baal-meon ,\f + \fr 13.17 \ft Bamoth-baal…: or, the high places of Baal, and house of Baal-meon\f*
And Jahazah , and Kedemoth , and Mephaath ,
And Kirjathaim , and Sibmah , and Zareth-shahar in the mount of the valley ,
And Beth-peor , and Ashdoth-pisgah , and Beth-jeshimoth ,\f + \fr 13.20 \ft Ashdoth-pisgah: or, springs of Pisgah, or, the hill\f*

And all the cities of the plain , and all the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites , which reigned in Heshbon , whom Moses smote with the princes of Midian , Evi , and Rekem , and Zur , and Hur , and Reba , \add which were\add* dukes of Sihon , dwelling in the country. \p
¶ Balaam also the son of Beor , the soothsayer , did the children of Israel slay with the sword among them that were slain by them.\f + \fr 13.22 \ft soothsayer: or, diviner\f*

And the border of the children of Reuben was Jordan , and the border \add thereof\add*. This \add was\add* the inheritance of the children of Reuben after their families , the cities and the villages thereof.
And Moses gave \add inheritance\add* unto the tribe of Gad , \add even\add* unto the children of Gad according to their families.
And their coast was Jazer , and all the cities of Gilead , and half the land of the children of Ammon , unto Aroer that \add is\add* before Rabbah ;
And from Heshbon unto Ramath-mizpeh , and Betonim ; and from Mahanaim unto the border of Debir ;

And in the valley , Beth-aram , and Beth-nimrah , and Succoth , and Zaphon , the rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon , Jordan and \add his\add* border , \add even\add* unto the edge of the sea of Chinnereth on the other side Jordan eastward.
This \add is\add* the inheritance of the children of Gad after their families , the cities , and their villages. \p
¶ And Moses gave \add inheritance\add* unto the half tribe of Manasseh : and \add this\add* was \add the possession\add* of the half tribe of the children of Manasseh by their families.
And their coast was from Mahanaim , all Bashan , all the kingdom of Og king of Bashan , and all the towns of Jair , which \add are\add* in Bashan , threescore cities :

And half Gilead , and Ashtaroth , and Edrei , cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan , \add were pertaining\add* unto the children of Machir the son of Manasseh , \add even\add* to the one half of the children of Machir by their families.
These \add are the countries\add* which Moses did distribute for inheritance in the plains of Moab , on the other side Jordan , by Jericho , eastward.
But unto the tribe of Levi Moses gave not \add any\add* inheritance : the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of Israel \add was\add* their inheritance , as he said unto them.
